The equipment and techniques used in this study are essentially those of Green et al. (1966) although two minor modifications are worthy of note
For the melting studies on Si 02, the boron nitride sleeve in the talc-boron nitride-graphite­pyrophyllite ceramic assembly of Green et al. (1966)
was replaced by pyrex glass. Calibration of this mod­ified assembly against the SiO2 (quartz)􀀝 SiO2
(coesite) transformation requires the application of  a -10% correction to nominal "piston-in" pressures.
Pressure was calibrated at 1000 C, using the following phase transformations as fixed points:
quartz/coesite (3.0 GPa), garnet/perovskite of CaGe03 (6.1 GPa), and coesite/stishovite (9.1 GPa).
The apparatus is a uniaxial split sphere system
Pressure values in the tetrahedral press were calibrated at room temperature  pressure, the proposal of Jeffery et al.
by measuring sharp resistance change in the flat strip samples of Bi, Ba, and Sn on the pressure-increase cycle. The values of transition
26 kbar for Bi I-II, 55 kbar for Ba I-II, 76 kbar for Bi lll-v, and 92 kbar for Sn I-II were adopted as fixed calibration points following
the proposal of Jeffery et al. [1960]
